hopobject.body: I was made redundant two months ago www.druge-bau.de For Senate Minority Leader Mitch McConnell of Kentucky, much lies in the balance as (once again) his party is poised to take over the body and make him majority leader – that is as long as he wins his 2014 re-election campaign. McConnell's prospects got bit murkier now that he not only faces a credible general election opponent in Democrat Alison Lundergan Grimes, but also a potentially well-funded primary challenger on the right in Matt Bevin.
